utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Kimberly, Juan wants to go to that one.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I would choose Ulysses S. Grant.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Oh, yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You know why?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You already have a flask with them in case we've ran out of booze.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Did you read his memoirs?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I actually did a book report on him on 8th grade, so I know a lot about him. Or at least I know with the encyclopedia Britannica told me.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No. But what she asked was a really good question because that's the best autobiography of a president. You know who wrote it?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Who?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Mark Twain.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Really. See we learn something every day here at The Five, and then we choose to forget it immediately afterwards. All right. Number three, third question, Jennifer B., what is your specialty dish, keep it clean, that you take to someone else's house for Thanksgiving.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I've got the one.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Let's start with Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, it's not me it's at least my wife. She takes sauerkraut. And this is so interesting because --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Mouthwatering.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You know for me, I'm not a big fan. But, turns out it's a tradition in her family, right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You hate your wife's sauerkraut.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I didn't say that.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You just did.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: You've said you're not a big fan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I said it's not my favorite.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: You've said you're not a big fan.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: At anybody sauerkraut.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: It is pretty -- it's pungent.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: It's pungent --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But what is really interesting to me is when I first became aware of this I would say, how can you guys cook sauerkraut, because it could have other thing like pig feet, you know, sort of black food, right? Ben then they had this sauerkraut -- it turns out that part of her family is a German heritage, and so they make sauerkraut.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Well.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Does the Germans allowed to celebrate thanksgiving, Juan?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Why not. What's wrong with German celebrating --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I'm just saying. Everybody knows.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You know what, Greg complains about identity politics. I think the biggest single ethnic group in America is German.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: OK. I was just thinking about German proper, but that's fine. Don't politicize the holiday, Juan.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Dana?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Wine.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Wine. Oh, I was going to say wine. I can't think of anything else.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I'm really good at bringing the wine. Nobody wants me to bring anything else, believe me.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Come on, kid, you could cook.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Kimberly?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I thought about your Kasam yesterday, by the way.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Kimberly thinks that a thanksgiving --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: No, no, no --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Why, because it's not American?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Mexican-American --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: You are taking my turn. I would love to bring, and I like to bring to anybody, banana pudding from Magnolia Bakery, and also one of their delicious apple pie and a pumpkin pie for dessert.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Nice.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Man, that banana pudding from Magnolia is outrageous.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Did I leave anybody else? Is that it?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: No. I'm going to K.G. on the dessert. I'll bring a pumpkin cheesecake, combo pumpkin pie cheesecake.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Do you make the cheesecake?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Absolutely not.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I might say, pumpkin cheesecake is heavy.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yeah, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I like the banana pudding. And of course, if you go across -- you know, and they have that -- what is that? Lemmon cake? That's outrageous.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: You like that a lot.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I like that a lot.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I only bring prescription medication and I don't share. That gets me through the evening.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: When you mix it with your wine.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, I don't.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes, you do,

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: America, don't do that. Michelle C. asks if you could ban one item, Jesse, this goes to you, from the thanksgiving menu, what would it be?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Juan's wife sauerkraut.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: No, let's see. Ban one item? I mean, what's to ban. It's all good. Is it stuffing?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Giblets are disgusting.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Giblets? What's that?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yeah, ban the innards. Get them out.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Get them out -- they should get them out.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: get them out.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: They've got to pull that out -- the plastic bag inside.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Does it work though? Does it cook it?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I mean it worked. You know, no one left.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: When was the last time you've cook the turkey, Kimberly?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: We'll get into that.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: A turkey quesadilla.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What would you ban?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I would ban -- first of all, I'm not a big fan of onions, number one. But not -- there was a plate of them anywhere. This is going to be seem weird.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I don't -- but they love sweet potatoes. I can't take.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's controversial.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Mashed potatoes. But I wouldn't ban sweet potatoes because so many people I love adore them.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think this will end up on all the blogs. They're going to come after you, Kimberly. You might want to issue a statement ahead of time.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Juan?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, so this is just between the five of us and the millions that watched. Somebody in my family makes cream cauliflower, just like, wow, like I don't know what to say.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yeah, I know you. Anything cream -- cream spinach is the only thing I could eat creamed.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That's good.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: What do you think about the green bean casserole?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, don't like that, especially with almond chips on top of it. They've always try to make it creative. If it's not good at its base, it's never going to get good.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: When you mess with it?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yeah. When you're trying -- you can trust that Quasimodo.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Recently, I have become a fan of Brussels sprouts, and you know why? Because they do them in a way that they become crisp on the outside.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes, you can like fry them a bit.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: It's like an area town you have to drive by really quickly. That's what Brussels sprouts smells like.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What is that?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Kind of like the smell when you walk by?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, you kind of got there first with that joke, but it's OK. I would say I would ban turkey. I think turkey is overrated. It's a very dry, boring meat.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well, you're not cooking it well. It could be very moist and succulent.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: If it was so good, why would they have gravy?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You don't put gravy on steak because steak doesn't need gravy.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: They put steak sauce on steak sometimes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's strange.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So you're now G. Kaput.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: You could deep fry it, and they have all those like --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Do you know how many fires have started by deep frying a turkey? Sixteen million a year.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I'm so sorry.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Where did you get that from?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: By the map on my head.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: This is thanksgiving, Gutfeld. Do you know that?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I know. I know. How about a big chicken? All right. This is from Dolores, so good of you, Dana, what do you do after thanksgiving dinner? Do you watch football, play a game, take a nap?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: When I was growing up we started tradition of going to the movies after thanksgiving dinner, but I think we're eating later this year, and we're guess of someone else. I'm going to try again play charades. That is fun.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That is fun.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I hate charades.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I'm not that good, really.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: But then, remember when we've played it at your house that time in South Carolina -- you know, when Greg wasn't --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I'm so mad about that trip.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: There are a lot of people who can't play charades, so I just find this whole game a little bit oppressive. Juan, what do you do after thanksgiving dinner?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I leave.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That best guest in the planet, Juan Williams.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Actually, we go to -- so I have Thanksgiving dinner at my brother's house, and then we have dessert and coffee at my wife's brother house, and then I fall asleep.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: But you didn't even like any of the food anywhere it seems.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No. I do like food --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Do you like sauerkraut?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: There you go.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Sounds like a great guy to have around.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I help with the dishes always, very good at doing dishes, and cleaning up, and wrapping up the leftovers. And then I love to watch football. And also, probably, have a glass of wine.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's nice. Usually what I do is I just wait for somebody to pick me up. The police are usually pretty nice about it. I usually have my own cell.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: In your unicorn sweater. Remember when Dana disinvited you to the Thanksgiving dinner?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, that was great. Come on over to the Thanksgiving dinner, and then don't --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: No. Because I was inviting -- I wasn't hosting, I was going to somebody's house and I don't know the people and it was a nice thing. And I was like, oh, he doesn't have anywhere to go, let's have him come. But then I thought, oh, he's going to hate it --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, fantastic. Well, so just do you know, I had a great time alone weeping at a closet.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Stabbing my Dana Perino doll that I made out of old socks. All right, last question from Paul K. -- let's go to you, Kimberly, how soon do you start listening to Christmas music?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I would say a safe bet would be December 1. My little Pandora, my SunOS, and then you could put like Christmas station. And I think it's quite cheerful.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Juan?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, this is a big complaint for me because I'm a big fan of channel 70 on XM which is love songs. Do you know that November 1st they changed to Christmas music?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's wrong.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Of you were Thanksgiving you'll be pretty angry.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But also, I mean, the crass commercialism, I mean, they just want you to buy -- I mean, even Back Friday now, really is now the Monday before thanksgiving.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, terrible. They need to rename that as well. Jesse?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Why do they need to rename that?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I just find the term Friday to be offensive.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Oh, I wasn't me.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Monday can get a lawyer.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: No, I'm fine. December 1st, bring it on. I'm ready.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Dana?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I only -- I never would actually choose to play it. It just happened to be around everywhere. Like, I went to get a manicure the other day, it's like early November and they're already playing it.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Womanicure.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Womanicure. Why does it have to be manicure? Womanicure. I'll practice saying that. Interesting fact about Christmas music, it's terrible because, you know, if you think about it -- if Christmas music was so good it would be played year-round.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: But it's not Christmas year-round.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: So they poised it on us for one month because they can't -- no one can stand it.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That's not true.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: It's terrible.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Because I think you know music, right? Phil Spector's Christmas music, outstanding that Wallace sound --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And where is he now?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He's serving life for murder.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He kills your ears, and then your life.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: The holiday celebrating life, and you listen to the one that takes us away.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think we can all agree here, Christmas music. All right. Much more to come on our Thanksgiving Facebook free-for-all. Stay right there.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Hello, again. And welcome back to The Five. We have more questions to answer from you this Thanksgiving. I'm going to start with Kimberly. This is from Kristy E. What is your favorite non-news show?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Wow. OK. Well, so I would say, it would have to be -- Greg, your head is on my shot.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Sorry.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Maybe it's Scandal or Grey's Anatomy.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Is that boring?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: No, that's good. People like those shows. If you're not watching news you can watch scandal, which is also kind like music.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Juan?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, I mean, I want to watch the NBA, so I watch my favorite team the Wizards or --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: That's not a show.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But it is a show. Believe me. It's like a soap opera, in fact. It follows -- that the way men follow sports, Dana. It's like, oh, imagine this person did this, this decision, or this call was ridiculous, or whatever --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Don't you watch anything besides sports?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, not much. Occasionally, I watch some of those HBO things --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Like, The Wire?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I love The Wire. I mean, you go back to Boardwalk Empire, The Sopranos, I love those.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: OK. All right, Jesse?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Something in this century please.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: It's not on anymore, The Office, was my favorite show.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: You watched the re-runs?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You're a lot like Michael Scott.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Thank you. I thought you're going to say Dwight.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I don't watch much TV anymore. I watch podcast. I come home I turn on a podcast. Right now, Norman McDonald's podcast, if you don't watch Norman, those are the best. I do watch BoJack Horsemen. They have a new series for BoJack Horsemen on Netflix, that's pretty good.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, I like younger, highly recommend that for a girl like Kimberly. I like Madam Secretary, that show does a very good job. I like Better Things.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What does it do?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: That does a good job like talking about working in foreign policy in the government.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Oh, really?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Is that what it is?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes, OK. All right. Jesse, we'll start with you. Melanie K. wants to know, what is something you think everyone should do, at least, once in their lives.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Let's see. Do once in their lives. That's a tough one because I haven't done everything.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: What would you like to do?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What would I like to do? You know, I don't know.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: All right. Should I start with somebody older? Juan, what do you think people should do once in their life?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I think you have to, sort of, go out in the woods by yourself and --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Vomit.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- get out.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Just get out quietly.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I mean, it's not that you necessarily are lost, but it's the idea that you go forward and it's a little bit like Walden Pond. You're just searching. It's hard to be by yourself these days.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: All right. Kimberly, why are you laughing?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Juan has never been hiking in his entire life.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Be eaten alive, or like kidnap by gypsy or something, or eaten by bugs.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: You understand the spirit of this question, Kimberly?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: The call of the question calls for a sense of all you have fun, exhilarating --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I would like to say go to Ireland -- yes, in particular, the southern part of Ireland, it's quite beautiful. And you go to the cliffs of Morris, which I think is one of the most spectacular thing I've ever seen in my life, and I really enjoyed it a lot. And then, I would just take a little sojourn up to Dublin to Trinity College, where I studied law, and take a look at the book of Cals.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: All right. How about you? What would you have everyone do?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Once your life you should be able feel the life of a stranger escape in your hands.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Happy Thanksgiving.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, I would say have a psychedelic experience.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Wow. Oh, no, I'm not doing that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I'm not saying how.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, you could meditate. You could meditate and have a psychedelic experience. You could listen to music and have a psychedelic experience. You could try certain kinds of natural substances in heaven, psychedelic experience.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I strongly discourage it.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I'm going to say everyone should go see Mt. Rushmore.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Where is that?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: South Dakota.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That was close.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You didn't even know.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: What I was thinking about when you say about psychedelic is, that when I was driving at with my answer was like, when I was 19, I was living in Africa for a while, and I went to live with a tribe. So they put me with the boys.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, they have a totally different view of the world. So, really, you're looking through the looking glass, because their view of the world, what's important to them is not important to us. Let me just tell you.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's the -- what I was getting at is that we are living in kind of an illusion. We don't really know --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: The matrix.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, the matrix. And it's like if you have it out of your brain experience, it will change you for the rest of your life.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Say no to drugs, everybody.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, I'm not talking about drugs. I'm talking about -- if you actually -- if you go on a meditation retreat. I've spent a week in a monastery. It was insane.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Did it help you?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Can you go back?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I ran away to a bar.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: All right. We're out of time. Oh, we have time for one more. OK. So we have to go quickly. If they made a movie of The Five, who would you get to play your part in the film and why? Greg?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Me? Obviously, Julia Roberts. I am like America's sweetheart. So I would say Julia Roberts would play me.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: OK, that's good. All right. Juan, do you have an answer?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Let see. I don't know.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: It's a tough one.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Meg Ryan would be great for Juan Williams.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Jesse, yours is easy, right?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Darth Vader.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I thought you're going to say Schwimmer.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Oh, is that a movie or a show.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, who would you get to play you? I mean, does he have to be an athlete?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Fine, Ross. Well, you've taken a lot of shots today, Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: No, I'm just trying to explain.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Who would play Dana? I think like Reese Witherspoon or something.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I like her.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What was that movie? The little too goody good shoes --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Legally blonde?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Is that it?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Election.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Election, yeah.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: How about you Kimberly? You can wrap us up.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Well, I could have taken Julia Roberts, but this weirdo took it.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: The fact that you did. OK. So, in that case, maybe -- I don't know.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Pretty Woman, Julia Roberts or -- oh, listen, she started it.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: No. I was thinking more of like the wholesome Julia Roberts.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Like in the Pelican Brief?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yeah --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: -- or Steel Magnolia, Julia Roberts.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I think Julia Roberts is so talented she can play the both of you. OK.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: All right. Stay right there, lots more of your questions straight ahead.

utterances.speaker: MIKE EMANUEL, FOX NEWS
utterances.utterance: I'm Mike Emanuel in Washington. President Trump and the first last served Thanksgiving lunch at a coast guard station near their Florida's home today. The president is thanking American military personnel for their service. He told the troops there winning big under his watch. U.S. and Japanese ships continue their search on this holiday for three missing American sailors. Their transport plane went down in the pacific yesterday, eight crew members were rescued, the navy says it has notified the next of kin that their whereabouts are unknown. You may be getting ready to head out the door to begin your holiday shopping. Many big stores are open tonight to get a head start on the traditional Black Friday stampede. The National Retail Federation expects sales to grow at least 3.6 percent like last year. Amazon is expected to take half of the holiday season's sales growth. I'm Mike Emanuel in Washington. Join me for "Special Report" at 6 p.m. Eastern for these stories and more. Now back to "The Five's" Thanksgiving special.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Welcome back. We're having a lot of fun answering your questions.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, we aren't.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Guess what? We have a whole lot more. Silencio, Greg. OK. So first question here. From Darlene P.: "If you could invent any holiday, what would you call it and what would it celebrate?" Ooh, this is kind of a tough one. Greg, do you have --?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Obviously, it would be Greg's Day and would celebrate all the great achievements of men under 5'6." Because oftentimes -- no, you know what? Short men -- if it wasn't for short men, the world would not exist. OK? Tall guys, they get to walk around. They always get the easy drink at the bar. But it's the short guy that builds the bar. It's the short guy that makes the money. We'll be right back.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: OK, that was compelling.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Writes the screenplay.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Exactly.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Napoleon and things like that. All right. Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I was going to say something -- I would like to have a day celebrating country music, because I think that that would be very fun; and Jesse might even actually participate.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What would you call that?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Country Day?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Country Day?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Country Day. National Country Day.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Sounds like a prep school.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Jesse, what you got?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Monday after the Super Bowl. You all don't have to come in hungover and tired.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Why isn't the Super Bowl on Saturday?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Call it Lazy Hangover Day.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: So obviously --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: This would be great. And Friday and Thursday.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: -- producers, Jesse wants that day off. OK. Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Let's see. I don't know. Maybe we could have a national kneeling day. Right? Yes. And protest. Right? So that everybody -- you know what?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I'm taking it.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: We understand what America is about. We understand people standing up for their rights in this country. And you know what? We celebrate American democracy and free speech.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And then the other side could say, "Ah, kneeling. How submissive. Kneel before us."

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes. Really.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Oh, my God.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That would be a comeback.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I just don't think that Colin Kaepernick is worthy of a national holiday. I believe that a lot of people are shaking their head, agreeing with me out there. OK. So how about this?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: What about you?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes, yes. I'm working on that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Don't rush her.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: OK, so I think how about -- OK. How about a holiday honoring all the victims of crime and national disasters that have suffered in, like, earthquakes and hurricanes and just, like, having a moment for everybody?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I like it.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes. Like give back on that day to all those particular causes and remember those people. I like it. I think it's quite good. OK. From Karyn P., "If you could be a Democrat for a day, who would you be?" Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I could be a Democrat for a day. Gee, I never thought about that. So let me think. A living, current Democrat? I don't know. I don't know. This is actually harder for me than the actress one.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I've got one. Dianne Feinstein.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: You would want to be her for a day?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes, I like her a lot. I know her from San Francisco. And she's on a lot of important committees. And so that I think her job would be interesting.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I like my friend Mary Anne Marsh.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes, she's quite nice.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes, she comes on the show once in a while.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Well, that's kind of creepy. You want to be your friend. Boy, she's going to call the police on you. You want to be her?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's a bit strange.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes, she should watch out.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Greggins, do you have anything?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, I'd do Juan Williams. That way I could sit --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Juan Williams.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I could sit over there on "The Five" and agree with me.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That's a good strategy.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Guess what, Greg? You're right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You're right! You're right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Kaboom. Kaboom. I can't believe at this table, everybody's right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Guess what?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Guess what?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: It could have been Jesse. He's got the right initials.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I would be -- I would be Obama, because he's making about a half a million dollars for a speech.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes, that's a --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Ka-ching. Guess what? Ka-ching.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Ka-ching. You win. You win.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Such a free-market guy. Love that consistency about you, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait. Hold on. Hold on.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Well, wouldn't you want to be yourself?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, no, I want to be a Republican. So if I'm a Republican, Kimberly, who do I get to be?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: And do you know what my answer is? The most impressive president I ever met.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Who?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: George H.W. Bush. And you know why?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: That's a very good answer.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Not only is he a secret agent, because he ran the CIA.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: He's a good baseball player, right? And guess what? He won the presidency. I mean, come on. How do you beat that guy?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: All right. Real quick from Nancy E., "Who has the messiest office here of 'The Five'?"

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Oh, that's so easy. It's Greg.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Who is it?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Greg.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: He's like little Pig-Pen.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: It's not messy. It's too small for the things that I have.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: There's like dust and things coming out of there.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: That's no excuse.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What is messy about it? What's in there that is messy?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I haven't been in there in a while.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I went in there once, and it was very dark.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. There's certain things I do in there that must be in the dark. But no.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: You're the messy -- you're very neat. You're very neat and organized. Dana and I obviously. Jesse, your like, office is pretty good.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, I know. You're surprised.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I'm totally surprised. Do you know whose office is a little bit crazy that currently is next to me? Brian Kilmeade.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I believe that.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Like weird stuff.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: He has a stand-up thing, where he doesn't sit down in the chair. A stand-up desk.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He has a lot of hair care products.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: That's you, by the way.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He has a system. It's not a hairpiece. It's a system. So he's basically got a hair tree. He's got a hair tree so he can pull parts of his hair. He goes, "Today I'll be this," and then he moves it around.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Oh, God. That's totally made up.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: When you pay that much for hair, it better be good.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Salacious lies. Well, it's a Q&A fiesta. All right. A little bit of a slam this Thanksgiving. Stay with us for more answers to your questions, all coming up.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Burp, it's Thanksgiving day. You know what time it is. Time to answer more of your questions posted on our Facebook page. How about this one? "If you could be a fly on the wall," Ms. Guilfoyle --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: " -- what private conversation, past or present, would you want to listen to?"

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Fly on the wall. This is kind of a tough one. Past or present conversation in general?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes. Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Not political?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Anything, anybody. Anything.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Uh --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Do you want to take a pass, and we go and then come back to you?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Maybe like a --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Go ahead.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I know. A conversation -- the last conversation that -- that President Trump had.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: The last one, why's that?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Because it would be the most current and most relevant.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK. All right. Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Maybe that Comey-Trump dinner that was very controversial and they have sparked this entire investigation. We might get to the bottom of things with that.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Good one. Good one. Good one.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. Dana Perino.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: There was a tape, but there's not a tape. I think that I would like to have listened in to conversations between Winston Churchill and Roosevelt, leading up to the Americans getting in the war.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Because he was suckering him in?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Suckering, no.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, wait.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I think Winston Churchill -- I don't think that was suckering. You think that that was bad for us to get in?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, no, not bad. It was good for us. In fact, I would have favored it, but I'm just noting that there was a lot of nationalistic instinct on the American part --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- not to get involved in a European conflict.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Right. And he persuaded them to do the right thing.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Correct, that's what I'm saying.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I would like to have -- I would like to have heard that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. Gregory.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: If I were a fly on the wall, I would like to be overhearing two other flies in my family, just to hear what they were saying about me.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: It's not going to be good.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No. Because then you'd find out if flies could really, you know, communicate. Which is kind of interesting. I always thought about it. They must have some kind of consciousness, flies.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: They must.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I'm not -- not really that interested.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: They must feel some -- they must feel some sort of pain when you crush them under your heels, Kimberly.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I do not step on flies.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Someone get a flyswatter.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I've seen the videos.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No. She pulls the wings off.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: No, I don't.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I'm teasing, I'm teasing.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: My gosh. Entomology 111, Insects and Human Affairs.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: She remembers everything.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes. And I wrote my paper on --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: She does too many drugs.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes, and I wrote my paper on "Entomophobia and Delusionary Parasitosis."

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Your memory is great.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, too.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Got an "A" plus in that class, an "A" plus. The highest grade in the class.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But I think you got "A" pluses in a lot of classes.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Well, that one in particular I remember.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Was that at Davis?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: U.C. Davis.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. Aggie.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I would go to -- I would listen as the fly on the wall to that conversation between Biden and Obama, where Obama counsels him against running against Hillary Clinton.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That'd be good.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Or how about --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You know what he'd say?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: "You swim in the nude. Don't run."

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Don't run. Or how about when -- when the Trump guys with that Russian, where the meeting was supposedly about adoption, remember that one?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Turned out to be more than one Russian, and it wasn't about adoption. Hmm. That would be interesting.

utterances.speaker: All right. Here's another question
utterances.utterance: "What's your favorite birthday gift that you received as a child and who gave it to you? And do you still have it?" Greg, you want to start?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You know, that's a good question. I would have to say, and this would surprise all of you, "The People's Almanac." Do you remember that big fat book?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: They gave it -- I remember how angry I was when I got it. Because you know you sneak -- you know where they hide the presents.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: That's a great one.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I opened up the closet, because I knew where they hid the key, and there was this box that was so heavy it could been a human head.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Eww.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And I'm thinking -- I'm hoping it's a human head. But no. So I'm thinking it could be anything. It's a book, and it's The People's Almanac. And I'm going -- and it was amazing. And then they did "The Book of Lists." Do you remember "The Book of Lists"?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: These were amazing. That's what got me to read.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That's cool.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, I don't have it anymore, because my godmother, Donna Nelson used to send me an angel food cake that she made.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Thank God you don't have it anymore.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes, it would be hard to have it anymore. And it was a really special gift that I got every year.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: How nice. And that's memorable. Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I know the gift that I didn't get, which I'm still upset about. I asked for the Michael Jackson leather jacket with all the zippers. My parents said it was too expensive. It only cost 30 bucks at the time. They gave me the glove instead where it was, like, you make your own glove. You put glue and sparkles.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's hilarious.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Not the same. That would been worth a lot of money.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: This is like the Nintendo. Like, you're upset about the --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Now somebody's going to send you the jacket.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I'm very happy about it. Andrea Streaker (ph), thank you very much.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Send you the Michael Jackson jacket.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Next week, can we have the "Mom Texts" after this show.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes. We're dialing it up. She's already sending something now.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Kimberly.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: What -- what gifts do I want?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes, birthday gift. Favorite birthday gift you ever got and who gave it to you?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I can't be answering these questions.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Which car?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: It says as a kid.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Which car?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: It says as a child. As a child.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: As a child, as a child. Thank you, Dana. Good save. As a child, well, can I be honest? I really did -- but you know the answer. I loved my Winnie the Pooh. Because that was, like, a special order when it came. And that was the one that my mom got me. But then it got given away to poor children, and I was very sad. And then somebody sent me one, which is very sweet.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, my folks weren't into gifts. So I don't remember any particular gifts.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's sad.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. But I will just say -- let's just say, there's one more question here about your favorite actor or actress. So just really quickly. Your favorite actor, actress?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I would have to say Lee Marvin.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Because --?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Lee Marvin. One of the greatest actors of all time.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Dana, we've got to go.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I think that time you were done.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You want to answer?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: They're going to cut us off.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Anybody have one?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Julia Roberts, "Pretty Woman."

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right, all right, all right. I like -- I like Angela Bassett. But you know.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: They're going to cut this whole thing.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Sigourney Weaver. "The Five" will be back in a flash.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: food, family and football AND more Facebook questions to answer this Thanksgiving. From Martha P., "If you could have Thanksgiving at the home of one of "The Five," which one would you choose? Kimberly.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes, absolutely.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I mean, isn't that the obvious --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Obvious choice.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No. Not at all. I would probably be at Juan's.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Why, because you like sauerkraut?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. WATTERS; I think Juan would have some interesting after-dinner stuff going on.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That is true.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Juan, is the answer at your house? You're going to stay at home.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, I think the mom of the show is Dana.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's a nice compliment. I'm going to agree.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: She's a very good entertainer.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Were there this summer. Very a nice spread.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Very nice spread.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: When was there?

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: You were there.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You were there. You just don't remember.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Jesse, I'd go to your house, because I really want to meet your girls.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Thank you. And my liberal mother.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes. Absolutely.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: My liberal mother.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I know.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's a book, by the way. You should GET -- write that right away. "My Liberal Mother."

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: In all my free time.

utterances.speaker: From Claudia W.
utterances.utterance: "Do you put up Christmas trees right after Thanksgiving?" I'm going to go with Gutfeld on this one.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, I do. Right after.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: On Friday you're erecting the tree.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I've got lights all over the roof.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: That is not true.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Santa and everything.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And I dress up as Santa.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: You don't even have a Christmas tree.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I went to Santa school, I'll have you know, in the '90s. If you want to look it up, for "Good Morning America." I actually went to Santa school to be a Santa.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: As an elf?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No. As Santa Claus.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: OK. Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: No, but I would buy a poinsettia.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's nice. Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Goodness. You know, the problem with it is not only do people put it up early, then they keep it around too long.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: It's like a fire hazard.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I would say you put it up. You know, my wife's birthday is, like, the 18th. So sometime in that week, I put up the Christmas tree.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Kimberly probably travels out east and chops her own tree down. Isn't that right, Kimberly?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, she actually went to Christmas tree class and got an "A" plus.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: How did you know? I am very good, setting up my little Christmas village with little stockings.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Trains.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes, and a train. Of course I do. And a beautiful tree and the whole works.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Very festive.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Gorgeous.

utterances.utterance: Wow. Wow. Harvey Weinstein.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I would agree with that.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I would agree with it, too.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I don't know. So the biggest turkey of the year. You guys have stumped me. I mean, let's get outside politics.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Wouldn't be the first time, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes. All right.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Won't be the last.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You agree. Weinstein?

utterances.utterance: I'm just going to say Hollywood.

utterances.utterance: Hollywood, the whole --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: One big giant bird. We should give them the bird.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Bird.

utterances.utterance: All right. "One More Question," next.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE (singing)
utterances.utterance: Have it your way, have it your way. Have it your way, at Burger king.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED FEMALE
utterances.utterance: May I help you sir?

utterances.utterance: Yes, you may. All right. "One More Question" this Thanksgiving, and it's a doozy. It's from Daniel K. He took hours to think of this one on Thanksgiving. Nice one, Daniel. You win a special award. Kimberly --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: -- "What are you thankful for and why?"

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: I'm very thankful and grateful and blessed to have my little boy Ronan in my life. He's absolutely wonderful. He's a sweetheart, and he treats other people so well and makes me very proud.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Aww, that's nice.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: And I love my brother, too.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's good. Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: So it's family. I mean, there's just no question. Especially, you know, this time of year, my son just moved into a new house with his bride to be. So it's going to be a wedding next year. My other son, you know, got married a year ago. And they're thinking about babies. And then, of course, I get to go hang out with granddaughters, identical twins who are five now, and a 7-year-old grandson. It's a lot of fun.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: So they're moving in before they get married, Juan?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes, indeed. Indeed.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Good to know. Going to hell.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Oh, wow.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Friends and family, obviously. We're spending time together on this holiday. And my beautiful twin daughters. And also the men and women in uniform who are --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: -- serving around the world and protecting us so we can all spend a safe and happy holiday here with our families.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I would say freedom and health and I'm -- I was really struck this year when I went back to Mercy Ships in Africa and just seeing how selfless the people are that volunteer there and how important health is, and it really is something to be thankful for and to take care of.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I'm also going to say -- I'm going to say friends and family. It's a great plan for phone service. That's a joke from five years ago.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Can I get on yours?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, you can. I'm -- I'm not going to say. I'm going to say thankful that this show is almost over, because that means I can get home --

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Eat more.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: -- put on my pajamas, open up a bottle of wine, and watch, like, "Law and Order" reruns until my eyes bleed.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: "SVU" marathon.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: "SVU" marathon.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: By the way, they trick you, because just as one ends, another one starts. And if you're mildly inebriated you don't know which one is -- you don't know if you're in the middle.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: Where it begins and where it ends.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And if you don't have a clock in your house, which I don't, it could be -- you could be at any time. You don't know what the table (ph) is doing.

utterances.speaker: GUILFOYLE
utterances.utterance: It could suck you in like that.

utterances.utterance: You know what I do? I just go and watch the commercials on FOX.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes?
